Mohammed Khubaib, originally from Pakistan, befriended girls and then 'hooked' them with vodka - normally vodka - in an attempt to make them ‘compliant’ to sexual advances .
The 43-year-old groomed vulnerable under-age girls by giving them money, gifts or cigarettes before plying them with alcohol .
Father of five, who lived in Peterborough with his wife and children, was found guilty of the charges against him by a jury at the Old Bailey in five hours .
He was remanded in custody and warned he faces a lengthy jail sentence .